Description: Ostracon, fragment of the neck of a light-brown pottery vessel, buff-coloured and grey in section, exterior covered with a cream-coloured slip and with faint traces of two lines of black-painted hieratic text, now smudged in places, identifying contents.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393144) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393144)
